<p>The Netherlands took control of Chinese-owned chipmaker Nexperia under the Goods Availability Act, saying the firm&#x27;s governance posed risks to Dutch and European economic security [apnews.com#6][abcnews.go.com#3]. Officials said the step aims to protect technology supplies, a move that could strain ties between the EU and China [bbc.com#4]. The government also worried about potential transfer of technology to Nexperia’s Chinese parent, Wingtech, which called the move “geopolitical bias”; Wingtech is already on a US blacklist [semafor.com#5]. The Financial Times reported the seizure followed a US ultimatum, underscoring how global pressure over critical tech is shaping national decisions [ft.com#1]. Russian outlet RT noted Dutch authorities cited risks to EU manufacturing capabilities in justifying the action [rt.com#2].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/WmXpOJwqYtEO9_k7VHBXGRKnxFrQKw6FmnvLqbyaGkauQvbw4zoGqLFH4ksJJPjs3unmjStNxQ_AUpGSBslQtt_JCIsuR2xVtDLvedqi2TOoUqnVOKBsfE2xUOS5mG-h_UWSMjABvrXMz24' alt='The Netherlands said it took control of chipmaker Nexperia citing governance and security risks.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Security rationale: The Dutch cited governance shortcomings and risks to Dutch and European economic security in taking control of Nexperia [apnews.com#6][abcnews.go.com#3].</li><li>Supply protection: Officials framed the intervention as protecting technology supplies, with potential to increase EU–China tensions [bbc.com#4].</li><li>Parent company: The Netherlands worried about possible tech transfer to Nexperia’s Chinese parent Wingtech; Wingtech called the move “geopolitical bias” and is on a US blacklist [semafor.com#5].</li><li>US pressure: The action followed a US ultimatum, according to the Financial Times, reflecting broader efforts to curb China’s tech advances [ft.com#1].</li><li>EU capability risk: Dutch authorities also cited risks to the EU’s manufacturing capabilities as justification for the step [rt.com#2].</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Dutch government: Authorities argued Nexperia’s governance could threaten Dutch and European economic security and moved to ensure the availability of critical technologies. (<a href='https://apnews.com/article/nexperia-wingtech-chips-netherlands-china-f1d3c84065cb61a1d645b64a3a2a68fc'>AP News</a>)</li><li>Wingtech (Nexperia’s parent): The company accused the Netherlands of “geopolitical bias” in response to the intervention. (<a href='https://www.semafor.com/article/10/13/2025/dutch-government-takes-control-of-china-owned-chipmaker-in-rare-intervention'>Semafor</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.ft.com/content/db019842-01a9-4488-a6a0-45d0e102536b'>Dutch seizure of chipmaker followed US ultimatum over Chinese chief</a> - ft.com</li><li><a href='https://www.rt.com/business/626384-china-eu-semiconductors-trade-tensions/'>EU state seizes Сhinese tech company</a> - rt.com</li><li><a href='https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/dutch-government-intervenes-chinese-owned-nexperia-governance-shortcomings-126462786'>Dutch government takes control of Chinese-owned chipmaker Nexperia over governance shortcomings</a> - abcnews.go.com</li><li><a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/ckgk21nng0vo'>Dutch government takes control of China-owned chip firm</a> - bbc.com</li><li><a href='https://www.semafor.com/article/10/13/2025/dutch-government-takes-control-of-china-owned-chipmaker-in-rare-intervention'>Dutch government takes control of China-owned chipmaker in rare intervention</a> - semafor.com</li><li><a href='https://apnews.com/article/nexperia-wingtech-chips-netherlands-china-f1d3c84065cb61a1d645b64a3a2a68fc'>The Dutch government invokes the Goods Availability Act to seize control of the Chinese-owned semiconductor manufacturer Nexperia, which is headquartered in Nijmegen, Gelderland, amid concerns that the company&#x27;s governance &quot;could pose a risk to Dutch and European economic security&quot;. (AP)</a> - apnews.com</li></ul>